  <brief_title>A Study of RO4917838 (Bitopertin) in Patients With Acute Exacerbation of Schizophrenia</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Phase II, Multi-center, Randomized, 4-week, Double-blind, Parallel Group, Placebo and Active-controlled Trial of the Safety and Efficacy of RO4917838 vs. Placebo in Patients With an Acute Exacerbation of Schizophrenia</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Hoffmann-La Roche</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Hoffmann-La Roche</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This randomized, double-blind, placebo- and active-controlled, parallel group study will
      evaluate the safety and efficacy of RO4917838 (bitopertin) in patients with acute
      exacerbation of schizophrenia. Patients will be randomized to receive either RO4917838 10 mg
      or RO4917838 30 mg or olanzapine 15 mg or placebo orally daily for 4 weeks as inpatients,
      with a 4-week follow-up period.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
